description:
How far can designers push an appearance if it can be worn instantly with simply a digital filter, abandoning the manufacturing restrictions and mindset of commercial and easy-to-produce fashion products? Or, can people be as bold as designers while rocking "technologic" designs?

The ambiguous epaulets on the shoulders and the grid balance of the "cage" part are seemingly contradictory designs that, like the lower metal surface that begins a little lower than the waist (despite the last "cage" line that defines that boundaries), can be worn with esteem at any robotic bagnio or at the virtual colosseum, even while simultaneously flaneuring in elegance over any ball.

This long dress, made in DFW, is cut from metallic anarchy of sleek lines, and it can be worn in any attitude, thanks to the wizardry of AR.

The design of garments was built on the idea of healing sounds. The Chladni plates (the visualization of sound vibrations) provide a therapeutic effect on the human body. The prints for the collection refer to images of the plate's surface and motion between various frequency values. Sooner or later, fashion tech specialists will create "healing garments" for daily use to make people calm down during anxiety, but now it's just a fantasy of the future of techwear.

hybrid down Cargo trousers with welt pockets, 3D printed surface as fabric embellishment.

These Down-cargo trousers recreate the symbiotic status between the larvae and cocoon.

The futuristic trend of avant-garde art of the XX century served as a source of inspiration for the creation of pants. The motifs of futuristic architecture were used in the design process of the shape of the pants, and the texture of the material resembles concrete.

All-over printed puff shirt with detachable half sleeves and buttons opening along the sides and shoulders. The print represents a dystopian desert with cities' famous monuments and buildings in ruins. The print was generated initially by artificial intelligence and readjusted by humans. The ironic message "Good morning, today is another day" refers to the nonchalance and careless behavior of a part of society concerning the planet's future.

You are a princess in the country of ginkgo trees, but you are not spoiled nor mild. You dress for the elegance and the glory of your home. The item is built based on real garment construction and all elements is simulation-able. 
It is build in Style3D, a software my company made, so my item is in .Sproj. Hope it's not a problem, I will also hand in obj, glb and gltf.

Bodycon dress with a combination of different textures: iridescent flounces, ribbed knit and digital satin with a camo-inspired print. The dress has a flounce structure arching around the body from the front neck towards the back, following the curved vertical panels.
The construction and inspirations are eclectic, coming from different types of garments such as bodycon dress, evening gown, and even elements from active wear in the form of ribbed inserts and cut out racer back detail. When creating this design I was exploring my interest in merging seemingly opposing elements into a refined whole, while creating a unique piece for a virtual wardrobe.

Low-rise digital cargo pants in u2k style as a symbol of the need to belong to a group with a similar views and the desire to stand out, to demonstrate one's own individuality. Trousers are complemented by naive infantile metal details which are the key elements in looks of this style. Let's play y2k aesthetics!

Plastic and metal melt and meet in this garment, giving shape to a new way of dressing, and  forming this long rubbery shining desperately wanted-to-be-touched skirt. This is a waxy look like piece, a low-waist skirt with a metal belt that twists sensually around the skin and has Eter’s signature logo.
Big and bubbly dress in therapeutic soft colors. Warm and cozy and protective.

Flared jeans with a combination of different textures: laser printed denim and shiny satin with a camo-inspired digital print. The pants have iridescent ribbed flounces inserted in leg panels. The legs are cut into curved vertical panels, based on various inspirations such as anatomic shapes, active- and shape-wear, denim wear, even cowboy trousers.  The construction and inspirations are eclectic, coming from different types of trousers, as I am interested in merging seemingly opposing elements into a refined whole.
When creating this design I was interested in exploring the trouser as a functional garment (taking inspiration for various types of 'leg wear'). Since this is a piece for a digital wardrobe I wanted to create something that draws details from the real world, but in a digital world would gain a different significance, as the functionality aspect is ruled out.
A sweet and wild two pieces set ready to use in your out of this world days.
The heavy burden. Rusty heavy sleeve, carried everywhere.  Anxiety.

Inspired by Y2K futurism and retro sci-fi, We created a military uniform for space soldiers. The design considers both dreamy mood and wearability which aims to let Zero10 users experience imaginary costumes alongside the sense of realistic fashion items.
Digital adult bib for jesting photo.

This outfit is inspired by the beauty of purple irises. The traditional meaning of irises is courage and fearlessness, and at the same time hope or solace.  For me personally, the flower also means fragility of life and relationships.

The Amphora digital dress is a representation of an ancient vase found on the bottom of the ocean. It has kept its legends for many millennia to be revealed to its discoverer. The Amphora dress is a symbiosis of the ancient Greek craft of ceramics, abstract art and digital fashion. The print you see is an abstract painting by a British artist, sculptor and writer Peter Bear.
Mantle-poncho with a collar. Along the edge of the fabric and on the collar are the famous Latin sayings in the Gothic style

Garment developed from the desire to propose an aggressive look but with an elegant fit. Like you have to go to Berghain but first you have dinner with relatives.
Genderless, if you like it, you can wear it.

Showing clothes as an independent object is always important to me as an artist.  Bright color, gradient, complex design tell more things about hard character.  The complex form simultaneously protects, but also calls for action.

The prints for the collection refer to images of the plate's surface and motion between various frequency values. Sooner or later, fashion tech specialists will create "healing garments" for daily use to make people calm down during anxiety, but now it's just a fantasy of the future of techwear.
REset is a piece of a collection inspired by the Tokyo Street style. A combination of fabric textures and colors, led by the art of @miancoArt merge creating this unique piece of an oversize vest.
These pants are definitely inspired Black Sabbath and that era. I imagined that Pope also wanted to hang out one day a year!

The source of inspiration for the creation of pants is the work of architect Zaha Hadid.  The material and shape of the pants were chosen based on the motifs of futuristic architecture. The basic principle of shaping in this project is the folds that emphasize the glaring material.

Strong, sensual, opulent: this piece combines a sharp construction with a soft, air-brushed print. The colors enhance the sculputural shape and emphasize the dynamic seamlines. The biker shorts repeat this style but in an intarsia knit.

I remember when I was little, and my mother used to cover our sofa with a beautiful hand-embroidered blanket depicting a radiant sun, in very bright colors.
The thing I loved most was turning the blanket and being amazed every single time, as the opposite side changed in appearance and color.
Seen through the eyes of a child, it could only be a magical blanket.
So, inspired by this childhood memory, I tried to recreate that magical feeling, with a design that hid a second truth. 
Front and back,
Day and Night.
This dress is made from assembled pieces of the universe. Belong to nowhere, home is in your mind!

“Burning For You” Dress envisions a future where fashion transcends the physical body or an event in the real world where our digital identities permeate our individual lifestyles to become the new reality.

“Burning For You” dives down into the terrorism and genocide that is taking place nowadays in Ukraine. The aggressive war Russia is doing toward the independent sovereign state is a crime to talk about. The future of this communication is here, in this dress to try on.

Dress of a form-fitting silhouette. Floor length. Long sleeve, pointed shoulder. The upper part of the dress is designed as a half bolero with three non-functional buttons. The lower part of the dress is a bell skirt. Dress made of dense material under the skin of a crocodile, skirt inserts made of printed silk.
Butterfly dress. Any girl wants to look airy, romantic and the most beautiful, like a butterfly at sunset.

Cropped armor jacket is a signature piece of the 19G brand, reflecting a key concept. Clothing as a symbol of protection of the individual, intangible values, morality, which is expressed through metal and rough textures. Recalling that the outer must protect the inner, which is the most valuable.
The costume is inspired by Gilese 581. It is one of the 100 closest stars to the solar system, this star is called red dwarf and is located 20.5 light years from planet Earth.

In "Rewind" series the author explores the topic of pollution and the need to reverse our process of slow self-destruction by marrying the concepts of progress and innovation with the idea of turning back to nature.

This bodycon dress is part of a collection paying homage to the queen of all colors: black. Achieving variation through different materials, surface characteristics and silhouettes is a significant part of the design process.
This tight fitted dress is made of textured latex and has a full zip on the back.
Digital adult romper  with print: "pacifier" - So funny look can back to infancy and present funny mood

ZERO is an edgy but casual spin on puffer-wear that draws Inspiration from retro anime and space suits; an iridescent and hydrophobic fit for the modern introvert. Pants have in-built programmable LED displays. You can't drown in this drip.

A lot of my designs are focused on bringing the digital and the natural together. In this case I my starting point was in the ethereal beauty of the shadows of plants in the wind. I found it fascinating how it contrasts with the way we view digital images, where we are able to see digital images through the light our screens emit, we can see these projections of plants by the absence of that light. The garments themselves are transparent in a purposefully artificial way to let the natural but digitised light shine from withing them.

I found it fascinating how it contrasts with the way we view digital images, where we are able to see digital images through the light our screens emit, we can see these projections of plants by the absence of that light. The garments themselves are transparent in a purposefully artificial way to let the natural but digitised light shine from withing them.

The jacket is designed to symbolise our use of language related to being human, though in a very digital space. We use the term "skin" to describe our digital avatars, when our skin is much more than simply our covering layer, it is our gateway of sensory interaction. This piece attempts to show skin being encapsulated in a stylised graphic pattern, reminiscent of computer chips.

Fitted corset. Draped skirt clinging to the sides layered over lace trousers. The look is made up of chiffon embroidered with lace cutouts and organic metallic shapes embedded in the lace.
I was interested in making creative textiles in 3D and working with lots of embroidery and drapery. I drew inspiration from Vivienne Westwood bridal wear and alexander McQueen's spring 2012 lace masks.

A bomber jacket with a combination of different textures: laser printed denim and shiny satin with a camo-inspired digital print. The jacket has an iridescent rib collar in the front that follows along the sleeves as a flounce structure.
I am interested in merging seemingly opposing elements into a refined whole and enjoy exploring creative pattern transformations. When creating this design I was exploring the functionality and history of the bomber jacket (also named as flight jacket, therefor the ribbed flounces suggesting the idea of wings) as a functional clothing piece in aviation -  given the current global context of war. While the colors and textures are completely opposing to the idea of army clothing: bright colors, iridescent, shiny textures.
Future tuxedo

A black leather dress with a boning top, and a chiffon detail on the shoulders. Gives the vibes of a girl go-getter, a girl who knows what she wants and she's not afraid to take it. A mafia girl-boss.
Particles, like pollen, are flying around the body. The iridescence effect gives freshness to the classic silhouette of this dress.
Like a lively, bubbly, and mysterious  aquatic creature roaming in the deep ocean, the indigo glow is flowing all over the veins with the breath.

The source of inspiration when designing the skirt was the structural geometry of the natural form - volcanic glass. The draperies of the skirt repeat the outlines of the obsidian shape, and the matte and glossy elements imitate the textures of natural stone.

The Matrix dress is about the technologies. Unusual materials and elements make it possible to delve into technology and "feel" the texture of clothing, as well as to get closer to the future. This dress is available in two colors.

The down jacket was created as a part of collection "Planet Parade". Mars is closely tied to the war in mass culture. This is why the look was inspired by Japanese traditional armor, Evangelion mechas and many other militaristic symbols.

description: I like to learn new fashion trends and try to use everything new and interesting in my work. The combination of a short top and tight short shorts with rough wide irregularly shaped jeans seemed very interesting to me.

The main idea is a creation of second skin for the soul - really passionate and full of life. Digital fashion let us fantasize about different shapes of our body and emotions that are raging inside. My work is an expression of inner fire.
Windbreaker - down jacket for any weather. Summer in the morning and winter in the evening. You never know what will happen in your life during the day.
Therapeutic soft light and straight flare fabric pants, with messy dark knotted bubble stiff top.  Yin and Yang. Soft and Strong.

This cape is a so far only digital garment that was inspired by ZeroWaste. Zero Waste is a method to completely consume the material without leaving 
any excess. Although regarding sustainability it‘s not the non plus 
ultra, but one brick in the sustainable philosophy. This cape means 
protection, modern construction, utility, transformation and 
flexibilty. The fit is based on principles of dressmaking, high quality, 
trendresearch and perfection in tailoring. 
Colour: Off-black, Enye-Tech-Green, Hyper-lilac
Digital material: Raw-denim, Heavy grain leather, Cotton stretch 
material
Sizes: Available in every size

The pale lagoon green color and the delicate folds of the Dew Dress draw inspiration from the serene image of morning dew. The dress encapsulates both the freshness of dawn and the intricate curves of dew droplets.
I was inspired by extraterrestrial life forms and I created something alien and fantastic. This item is from completely different planet.

FASHION&TECH IN A FANTASTIC OUTFIT. This is a look all about connections and information encripted in this amazing texture. Do you want to find it out? Wear it! Connect with it! Share your history and let this information to be saved and registered between materials and colors.

description: Betta Fish is a dress inspired by the colors, pleated fins, and flowy body of the Betta fish. I added my signature touch, the gold details, to add a fancy element to the dress.

Showing clothes as an independent object is always important to me as an artist.  Bright color, gradient, complex design tell more things about hard character.  The complex form simultaneously protects, but also calls for action.

Genesis and Genetics are two words for which the dress's name was born.
We are living in an era where human beings need to re-connect with their beginning, with nature, and feel it as part of their DNA if they want to continue living in this world.
The dress represents this new form of life, a balanced fusion of organic shapes and different materials (especially organic silk) layering and overlapping in harmony.
The colors contrast in order to represent the never-ending cycle of life and passing of time, vibrant and muted, new and old, origins and tradition in balance with new ways and contemporary visions.

The idea behind this garment was to create something that can mix the simplicity of a bomber jacket with a complex and appealing design. The colors I have chosen have the
purpose to recall hot places in contrast to the classic use of a bomber jacket to fight the cold.
The design aims to stimulate the imagination of the wearer giving him total control over what he sees in the shapes of the jacket.
I choose to develop this garment in 3D because realize it in real live could be very expensive but I still wanted to evaluate the impact of such design on the public.

Conceived from unwearable materials, Eter explores the infinite possibilities of the virtual and creates new digital wear. This garment is a two layered tank top: a translucent glassy top covered in hard melting metal, creating a balance between exploring fantasies through clothing and desirable items that we would love to have in real life.
This is the digital version of our John Jacket which we were inspired by the music and social position of the legendary John Lennon. it's a mix of biker jackets and hippie ponchos

Live fast and overthink. 
Have you ever been out and about feeling luscious and suddenly the dread for the future knocked in? 
This spicy, coquettish dress is here to ask everyone. The answer is  always: enjoy the moment.
Heavy chest. Anxiety. What comes next. Perfect pants.
A velvet off-shoulder black dress with a slit for when the hot girl is widowed in her 30s. Sad yet sophisticated and elegant.

This dress was inspired by the sunset, it's made in a gradient fabric that goes between orange and purple. the dress has five layers of accordion pleats that flare out at the end to reach that touch of gold like the sunset sky has these subtle sunrays.

The realization has come that you have failed to protect yourself from the influence of white noise (the opinions of others, the media, the daily routine, groundhog day, the noise of cars and the noise of human life, the monotonous cycle).

White noise overrides the voice of my inner self. This noise makes it hard to hear and understand yourself.
Nastro dress is an elegant and essential dress. It wraps the shape of the body enhancing harmonious lines. The material is iridescent and enameled, enveloping you like an ancient goddess.

I was born in a small village inside the hills, surrounded of green. The ispiration for Coraline coat is born from here, I mixed the mood from my grandma's old photographs with every shades of green that I see around me every day.

All products were created with the support of the new digital atelier A.D.A. (Alkali Digital Atelier)
The first costume "Pieces" is created for people, who wants to try clothes that cannot be in realitys are created for any gender and they can be worn separately.
Digital Dress [Sakura (new beginnings) + iPhone (accessibility to tech) + Eyes (navigating warnings)] = From the Dev桜ce

The Radiance dress is inspired by the role of women in today's world. And metaphorically all the roles are reflected in this attire. The armor symbolizes the function of protecting the family, children and oneself. Luminous side elements with a train refer to the social component, where they achieve success, create new projects and leave a significant mark on history. An animated twinkling centerpiece front and back shows how women fill the world with beauty and brilliance, and how they change the world around them.
Spacial Jumper with iridiscent and translucent materials

This dress is simple from a pattern-making point of view but has the twist of lots of ostrich feathers attatched to the skirt. This and the colours chosen make the wearer stand out from the mass for sure!
Flowy yet elegant go-to staple for a chic-classic and fierce aesthetic.
The hot and the cold. The natural and the mystical. Dreamy.
A playful oversized digital puffer jacket with the ability to express love with an animated heart in AR.
This inflatable dress was created as a part of collection "Planet Parade". In Roman mythology Venus is a goddess of love and beauty. This is why the piece of garment has a very mild feminine look.

Inspired by the feelings, Thoughts and conversations that astronauts have throughout their journeys, Thinking that somehow all these stay inside the ship, keeping their joys, discoveries and uncertainties. This design reflects all the moments and experiences they lived through and makes us remember everything they have achieved.

The NeoDIABLO piece is the result of the junction of references that border the Y2K aesthetic with a lifestile of those who love and consume content aimed at TRASH terror. The futuristic with the nostalgic resulted in a jacket that represents this union of references.

Olska Green (founder of the Ecoolska brand and fashion designer) was inspired by biodiversity of wonderful underwater world. The beauty of nature is the best source of inspiration. Algae plays a significant and integral role in the marine ecosystem. It is very important for balancing marine ecosystems and plays a role in thwarting climate change. You can feel like a mermaid from a fairy tale if you virtually try on this flowing elegant digital dress.

I am looking for inspiration in the real world and I want to reflect its beauty in the virtual world. I wanted to create an unusual dress design and complement it with an interesting texture. I hope I managed to get your attention. thanks!
